{"TopicId":197925,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Calculating Optimal Ascent Profile?","CreatedByName":"eM-Krow","CreatedById":206322,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-05T02:44:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"eM-Krow","CreatedById":206322,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-05T02:44:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen a few posts thrown around about this here and there, on this site and off, but haven\u0027t really seen anyone actually say they\u0027ve made a way to calculate it yet (without something called \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E? Which I haven\u0027t checked out since from contextual clues I assume it was basically a loop to check the optimal profile). Anyone have any data on this at all?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf there is something like that, is it possible to throw \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E, Dry/Wet Masses, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E variables into it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-05T02:55:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022167020\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2197244547\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/144538-delta-v-calculations-accuracy/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2692269\u0026amp;embedComment=2692269\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:294px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately, you have to solve an integral (many of the terms of which are unknowable). Here\u0027s the only code I know of, which settles for a rough approximation:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://git